      "writtenOn": "2020-05-27T12:39:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The point of using surface.requestAnimationFrame is that you don\u0027t have need to call surface.flush() (which is why we made it unexported/private)\n\nDoes this mean we do need to make flush public on Surface? Is there another way we can do this, maybe with a callback?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 80,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 80,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "81b86d32fda1d97549a6b571d4d5f8f9bcbed8da",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
